tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, suggesting impaired glucose metabolism or early diabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Chloride is slightly elevated and total CO₂ is mildly decreased, which may indicate a mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Renal function and other electrolytes are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
